@Minniehahah @Tinder You have to be patient. 

You don't buy a share price you buy a piece of a company.  

Evaluate the growth in what you own, not the price given by the market. The signs are there from $MSFT $GOOG & $AMZN that the most amazing business at scale is the cloud. That's the golden goose for $BABA , e-commerce will grow healthy but cloud may very well push this company into the trillions. The cloud is about $200B in U.S. but only $20B in China. It's compounding over 40% a year, so that's a 5X in 5 years and that only gets cloud to half US at  $100B. $BABA has 40% of the cloud, ask yourself what a $40B cloud business alone is worth, this ignores the e-commerce section. Cloud just got EBITDA positive last year.

Sentiment ebbs and flows, look at energy which was a dog in 2020 now it's the hottest thing in the market. You habe to be patient.
